# Email MCP Server Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your credentials
# NEVER commit .env to git

---

# Email Provider Selection
EMAIL_PROVIDER=smtp  # Options: smtp, gmail

---

# SMTP Configuration (if using SMTP provider)
# Recommended for Gmail, Outlook, etc.

SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USE_TLS=true

# Gmail: Your email address
SMTP_EMAIL=your_email@gmail.com

# Gmail: 16-character app password (NOT your regular password!)
# Get from: https://myaccount.google.com/security
# Then: App passwords → Select Mail and Windows Computer
SMTP_PASSWORD=xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx

# Display name for sent emails
SMTP_FROM_NAME=Your Name

---

# Gmail API Configuration (if using Gmail API provider)
# Alternative to SMTP - uses same OAuth as Gmail Watcher

EMAIL_GMAIL_CREDENTIALS_PATH=~/.secrets/gmail_credentials.json
EMAIL_GMAIL_USER=your_email@gmail.com

---

# MCP Server Configuration

# Port to listen on
MCP_PORT=3001

# Log file location
LOG_FILE=~/.logs/email_mcp.log

# Log level: debug, info, warn, error
LOG_LEVEL=info

---

# Email Sending Settings

# Maximum email size (default 25MB)
MAX_EMAIL_SIZE=25000000

# Restrict recipients to specific domain (* = any)
ALLOWED_RECIPIENTS_DOMAIN=*

# Require manual approval before sending (Phase 6)
REQUIRE_APPROVAL=false

---

# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS

## For Gmail with SMTP (Recommended)

1. Go to https://myaccount.google.com/security
2. Enable "2-Step Verification" if not already done
3. Go to "App passwords" (at bottom of security page)
4. Select "Mail" and "Windows Computer"
5. Copy the 16-character password
6. Set in this file:
   - SMTP_EMAIL=your_email@gmail.com
   - SMTP_PASSWORD=xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx (the 16 characters)
   - SMTP_FROM_NAME=Your Name

## For Gmail with Gmail API

1. Use credentials.json from Phase 2 (Gmail Watcher)
2. If you don't have it:
   - Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
   - Create new project → Enable Gmail API
   - Create OAuth2 credentials (Desktop app)
   - Download JSON file
   - Save to ~/.secrets/gmail_credentials.json
3. Set in this file:
   - EMAIL_GMAIL_CREDENTIALS_PATH=~/.secrets/gmail_credentials.json
   - EMAIL_GMAIL_USER=your_email@gmail.com

## For Other Providers (Outlook, Custom SMTP)

1. Get SMTP credentials from your email provider
2. Set SMTP_HOST, SMTP_PORT, SMTP_EMAIL, SMTP_PASSWORD
3. Example (Outlook):
   - SMTP_HOST=smtp-mail.outlook.com
   - SMTP_PORT=587
   - SMTP_EMAIL=your_email@outlook.com
   - SMTP_PASSWORD=your_app_password

---

# SECURITY REMINDERS

✅ DO:
- Keep SMTP_PASSWORD and credentials file secure
- Use app-specific passwords (not main account password)
- Never commit .env to git
- Set .env permissions: chmod 600 .env
- Use dedicated automation account if possible

❌ DON'T:
- Store passwords in plain text (wait, we do this - see above about app passwords!)
- Share .env file with others
- Commit .env to version control
- Use your main account password
- Run this server on public networks

---

# FILE PERMISSIONS

After creating .env:
```bash
chmod 600 .env
```

This restricts file access to owner only.

---

# NEXT STEPS

1. Create .env file with your configuration
2. Run: npm install
3. Run: bash scripts/start-server.sh
4. Test: python3 scripts/verify.py
5. Send test email: See SKILL.md for examples

---

# TESTING

Before using in production, test with:

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/send-email \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "to": "test@example.com",
    "subject": "Test Email",
    "body": "This is a test email"
  }'
```

Check logs:
```bash
tail -f ~/.logs/email_mcp.log
```

---
